#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:23.1"
msgid "Apissu maṃ, bhāradvāja, devatā disvā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Then some deities saw me and said:"

msgctxt "mn100:23.2"
msgid "‘kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama is dead.’"

msgctxt "mn100:23.3"
msgid "Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Others said:"

msgctxt "mn100:23.4"
msgid "‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, api ca kālaṃ karotī’ti."
msgstr "‘He’s not dead, but he’s dying.’"

msgctxt "mn100:23.5"
msgid "Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Others said:"

msgctxt "mn100:23.6"
msgid "‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, nāpi kālaṃ karoti;"
msgstr ""
"‘He’s not dead or dying. The ascetic Gotama is a perfected one, for that is "
"how the perfected ones live.’"

msgctxt "mn100:23.7"
msgid "arahaṃ samaṇo gotamo, vihāro tveva so arahato evarūpo hotī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:24.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn100:24.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr "‘Why don’t I practice completely cutting off food?’"

msgctxt "mn100:24.3"
msgid "Atha kho maṃ, bhāradvāja, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "But deities came to me and said:"

msgctxt "mn100:24.4"
msgid "‘mā kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajji."
msgstr "‘Good sir, don’t practice totally cutting off food."

msgctxt "mn100:24.5"
msgid ""
"Sace kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjissasi, tassa te "
"mayaṃ dibbaṃ ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāressāma."
msgstr ""
"If you do, we’ll infuse divine nectar into your pores and you will live on "
"that.’"

msgctxt "mn100:24.6"
msgid "Tāya tvaṃ yāpessasī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn100:24.7"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn100:24.8"
msgid ""
"‘ahañceva kho pana sabbaso ajajjitaṃ paṭijāneyyaṃ, imā ca me devatā dibbaṃ "
"ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāreyyuṃ, tāya cāhaṃ yāpeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If I claim to be completely fasting while these deities are infusing divine "
"nectar in my pores, that would be a lie on my part.’"

msgctxt "mn100:24.9"
msgid "Taṃ mamassa musā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn100:24.10"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, tā devatā paccācikkhāmi, ‘halan’ti vadāmi."
msgstr "So I dismissed those deities, saying, ‘There’s no need.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:25.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn100:25.2"
msgid ""
"‘yannūnāhaṃ thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā "
"muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā "
"hareṇukayūsan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Why don’t I just take a little bit of food each time, a cup of broth made "
"from mung beans, lentils, chick peas, or green gram.’"

msgctxt "mn100:25.3"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi "
"vā muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā "
"hareṇukayūsaṃ."
msgstr "So that’s what I did,"

msgctxt "mn100:25.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhārayato pasataṃ pasataṃ, "
"yadi vā muggayūsaṃ, yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ, yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ, yadi vā "
"hareṇukayūsaṃ, adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti."
msgstr "until my body became extremely emaciated."

msgctxt "mn100:25.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma āsītikapabbāni vā kāḷapabbāni vā; evamevassu me "
"aṅgapaccaṅgāni bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, my limbs became like the joints of an eighty year "
"old or a corpse,"

msgctxt "mn100:25.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma oṭṭhapadaṃ; evamevassu me ānisadaṃ hoti tāyevappāhāratāya;"
msgstr "my bottom became like a camel’s hoof,"

msgctxt "mn100:25.7"
msgid ""
"seyyathāpi nāma vaṭṭanāvaḷī; evamevassu me piṭṭhikaṇṭako uṇṇatāvanato hoti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr "my vertebrae stuck out like beads on a string,"

msgctxt "mn100:25.8"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma jarasālāya gopānasiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti; evamevassu me "
"phāsuḷiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr "and my ribs were as gaunt as the broken-down rafters on an old barn."

msgctxt "mn100:25.9"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma gambhīre udapāne udakatārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti;"
" evamevassu me akkhikūpesu akkhitārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, the gleam of my eyes sank deep in their sockets, "
"like the gleam of water sunk deep down a well."

msgctxt "mn100:25.10"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma tittakālābu āmakacchinno vātātapena samphuṭito hoti "
"sammilāto; evamevassu me sīsacchavi samphuṭitā hoti sammilātā "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, my scalp shriveled and withered like a green bitter-"
"gourd in the wind and sun."

msgctxt "mn100:25.11"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, ‘udaracchaviṃ parimasissāmī’ti piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃyeva "
"pariggaṇhāmi, ‘piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ parimasissāmī’ti udaracchaviṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi;"
" yāvassu me, bhāradvāja, udaracchavi piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ allīnā hoti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, the skin of my belly stuck to my backbone, so that "
"when I tried to rub the skin of my belly I grabbed my backbone, and when I "
"tried to rub my backbone I rubbed the skin of my belly."

msgctxt "mn100:25.12"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, ‘vaccaṃ vā muttaṃ vā karissāmī’ti tattheva avakujjo "
"papatāmi tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, when I tried to urinate or defecate I fell face "
"down right there."

msgctxt "mn100:25.13"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, imameva kāyaṃ assāsento pāṇinā gattāni anumajjāmi. "
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, pāṇinā gattāni anumajjato pūtimūlāni lomāni "
"kāyasmā papatanti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, when I tried to relieve my body by rubbing my limbs "
"with my hands, the hair, rotted at its roots, fell out."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:26.1"
msgid ""
"Apissu maṃ, bhāradvāja, manussā disvā evamāhaṃsu: ‘kāḷo samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "Then some people saw me and said: ‘The ascetic Gotama is black.’"

msgctxt "mn100:26.2"
msgid ""
"Ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo, sāmo samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "Some said: ‘He’s not black, he’s brown.’"

msgctxt "mn100:26.3"
msgid ""
"Ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo napi sāmo, maṅguracchavi "
"samaṇo gotamo’ti;"
msgstr ""
"Some said: ‘He’s neither black nor brown. The ascetic Gotama has tawny skin.’"

msgctxt "mn100:26.4"
msgid ""
"yāvassu me, bhāradvāja, tāva parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto upahato hoti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"That’s how far the pure, bright complexion of my skin had been ruined by "
"taking so little food."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:27.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn100:27.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye kho keci atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā "
"kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayiṃsu, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo;"
msgstr ""
"‘Whatever ascetics and brahmins have experienced painful, sharp, severe, "
"acute feelings due to overexertion—whether in the past, future, or present—"
"this is as far as it goes, no-one has done more than this."

msgctxt "mn100:27.3"
msgid ""
"yepi hi keci anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā "
"kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayissanti, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn100:27.4"
msgid ""
"yepi hi keci etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā "
"kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, etāvaparamaṃ, nayito bhiyyo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn100:27.5"
msgid ""
"Na kho panāhaṃ imāya kaṭukāya dukkarakārikāya adhigacchāmi uttari "
"manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But I have not achieved any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision "
"worthy of the noble ones by this severe, gruelling work."

msgctxt "mn100:27.6"
msgid "Siyā nu kho añño maggo bodhāyā’ti?"
msgstr "Could there be another path to awakening?’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:28.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn100:28.2"
msgid ""
"‘abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ pitu sakkassa kammante sītāya jambucchāyāya nisinno "
"vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ "
"pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharitā."
msgstr ""
"‘I recall sitting in the cool shade of the rose-apple tree while my father "
"the Sakyan was off working. Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded "
"from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, "
"which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind "
"and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "mn100:28.3"
msgid "Siyā nu kho eso maggo bodhāyā’ti?"
msgstr "Could that be the path to awakening?’"

msgctxt "mn100:28.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, satānusāri viññāṇaṃ ahosi:"
msgstr "Stemming from that memory came the realization:"

msgctxt "mn100:28.5"
msgid "‘eseva maggo bodhāyā’ti."
msgstr "‘<em>That</em> is the path to awakening!’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:29.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn100:29.2"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi "
"aññatra akusalehi dhammehī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Why am I afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual "
"pleasures or unskillful qualities?’"

msgctxt "mn100:29.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn100:29.4"
msgid ""
"‘na kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi aññatra "
"akusalehi dhammehī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’m not afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual "
"pleasures or unskillful qualities.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya30"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:30.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhāradvāja, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to me:"

msgctxt "mn100:30.2"
msgid ""
"‘na kho taṃ sukaraṃ sukhaṃ adhigantuṃ evaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyena."
msgstr ""
"‘I can’t achieve that pleasure with a body so excessively emaciated. Why don’"
"t I eat some solid food, some rice and porridge?’"

msgctxt "mn100:30.3"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ odanakummāsan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn100:30.4"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ."
msgstr "So I ate some solid food."

msgctxt "mn100:30.5"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana maṃ, bhāradvāja, samayena pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū paccupaṭṭhitā "
"honti:"
msgstr "Now at that time the five mendicants were attending on me, thinking:"

msgctxt "mn100:30.6"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ adhigamissati taṃ no ārocessatī’ti."
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama will tell us of any truth that he realizes.’"

msgctxt "mn100:30.7"
msgid ""
"Yato kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ, atha me "
"te pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū nibbijja pakkamiṃsu:"
msgstr ""
"But when I ate some solid food, they got disillusioned and left, saying:"

msgctxt "mn100:30.8"
msgid "‘bāhulliko samaṇo gotamo padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has become indulgent; he’s strayed from the struggle and "
"fallen into indulgence.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya31-33"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:31-33.1"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhāradvāja, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāretvā balaṃ gahetvā vivicceva "
"kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"After eating solid food and gathering my strength, quite secluded from "
"sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and "
"remained in the first absorption …"

msgctxt "mn100:31-33.2"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were stilled, I entered "
"and remained in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "mn100:31-33.3"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "mn100:31-33.4"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya34"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:34.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, spotless, "
"rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it "
"toward recollection of past lives."

msgctxt "mn100:34.2"
msgid ""
"So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi "
"jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi."
msgstr ""
"I recollected many past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, "
"twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand "
"rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world "
"evolving, many eons of the world contracting and evolving. And so I "
"recollected my many kinds of past lives, with features and details."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya35"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:35.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhāradvāja, rattiyā paṭhame yāme paṭhamā vijjā adhigatā, "
msgstr ""
"This was the first knowledge, which I achieved in the first watch of the "
"night. "

msgctxt "mn100:35.2"
msgid ""
"avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; yathā taṃ "
"appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and "
"light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya36-38"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:36-38.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then, with my mind collected, purified, cleansed, flawless, free from "
"defilements, soft, wieldy, steady, and imperturbable, I directed it to the "
"knowledge of the arising and passing away of beings."

msgctxt "mn100:36-38.2"
msgid ""
"So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage "
"satte pajānāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I saw sentient beings "
"passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in "
"a good place or a bad place. I understood how sentient beings are reborn "
"according to their deeds …"

msgctxt "mn100:36-38.3"
msgid "ayaṃ kho me, bhāradvāja, rattiyā majjhime yāme dutiyā "
msgstr ""
"This was the second knowledge, which I achieved in the middle watch of the "
"night. "

msgctxt "mn100:36-38.4"
msgid ""
"vijjā adhigatā, avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; "
"yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and "
"light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya39"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:39.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr ""
"When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, spotless, "
"rid of taints, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I turned it "
"toward knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "mn100:39.2"
msgid ""
"So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘"
"ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"I truly understood: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ …"
" ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to "
"the cessation of suffering’."

msgctxt "mn100:39.3"
msgid ""
"‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ "
"āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I truly understood: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya40"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:40.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa me evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccittha, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha."
msgstr ""
"Knowing and seeing like this, my mind was freed from the defilements of "
"sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance."

msgctxt "mn100:40.2"
msgid "Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "When it was freed, I knew it was freed,"

msgctxt "mn100:40.3"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"I understood: ‘Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya41"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:41.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, bhāradvāja, rattiyā pacchime yāme tatiyā "
msgstr ""
"This was the third knowledge, which I achieved in the last watch of the "
"night. "

msgctxt "mn100:41.2"
msgid ""
"vijjā adhigatā, avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno; "
"yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato”ti."
msgstr ""
"Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and "
"light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya42"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.213"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:42.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, saṅgāravo māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Saṅgārava said to the Buddha:"

# Here, aṭṭhita is ā+ṭhita
#. VAR: aṭṭhitavataṃ → aṭṭhitavata (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: sappurisavataṃ → sappurisavata (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn100:42.2"
msgid ""
"“aṭṭhitavataṃ bhoto gotamassa padhānaṃ ahosi, sappurisavataṃ bhoto gotamassa "
"padhānaṃ ahosi;"
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama’s effort was steadfast and appropriate for a good person,"

msgctxt "mn100:42.3"
msgid "yathā taṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr "since he is a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha."

#. VAR: atthi devā”ti → adhidevāti (mr)
msgctxt "mn100:42.4"
msgid "Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, atthi devā”ti?"
msgstr "But Master Gotama, do gods absolutely exist?”"

# The idiomatic instrumental thanaso is used in two ways in the suttas: “imediately, on the spot”, and “in terms of cause”, where it is usually paired with hetuso. I take it in the latter sense. The Buddha was phrasing his reply so as to avoid the implied metaphysical absolutism in the question.
#. VAR: Ṭhānaso metaṃ → ṭhānaso kho panetaṃ (s1-3, km) | kho panetaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn100:42.5"
msgid "“Ṭhānaso metaṃ, bhāradvāja, viditaṃ yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "“I’ve understood the existence of gods in terms of causes.”"

#. VAR: adhidevā”ti → atthi devāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | atidevāti (?)
msgctxt "mn100:42.6"
msgid "adhidevā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn100:42.7"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, ‘atthi devā’ti puṭṭho samāno ‘ṭhānaso metaṃ, "
"bhāradvāja, viditaṃ yadidaṃ adhidevā’ti vadesi."
msgstr ""
"“But Master Gotama, when asked ‘Do gods exist?’ why did you say that you "
"have understood the existence of gods in terms of causes?"

msgctxt "mn100:42.8"
msgid "Nanu, bho gotama, evaṃ sante tucchā musā hotī”ti?"
msgstr "If that’s the case, isn’t it a baseless lie?”"

#. VAR: puṭṭho samāno ‘atthi devā’ti yo vadeyya, ‘ṭhānaso me viditā’ti → ṭhānaso viditā me viditāti (s1-3, km, pts1) | ṭhānaso me viditā atidevāti (?)
msgctxt "mn100:42.9"
msgid ""
"“‘Atthi devā’ti, bhāradvāja, puṭṭho samāno ‘atthi devā’ti yo vadeyya, ‘"
"ṭhānaso me viditā’ti yo vadeyya;"
msgstr ""
"“When asked ‘Do gods exist’, whether you reply ‘Gods exist’ or ‘I’ve "
"understood it in terms of causes’"

#. VAR: gantabbaṃ → gantuṃ vā (s1-3, km) | gantuṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn100:42.10"
msgid "atha khvettha viññunā purisena ekaṃsena niṭṭhaṃ gantabbaṃ yadidaṃ:"
msgstr "a sensible person would come to the definite conclusion that"

msgctxt "mn100:42.11"
msgid "‘atthi devā’”ti."
msgstr "gods exist.”"

#. VAR: gotamo ādikeneva na byākāsī”ti → gotamo ādikeneva byākāsīti (mr) | gotamo atthi devāti na byākāsīti (?)
msgctxt "mn100:42.12"
msgid "“Kissa pana me bhavaṃ gotamo ādikeneva na byākāsī”ti?"
msgstr "“But why didn’t you say that in the first place?”"

msgctxt "mn100:42.13"
msgid "“Uccena sammataṃ kho etaṃ, bhāradvāja, lokasmiṃ yadidaṃ:"
msgstr "“It’s widely agreed in the world that"

msgctxt "mn100:42.14"
msgid "‘atthi devā’”ti."
msgstr "gods exist.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya43"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:43.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, saṅgāravo māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Saṅgārava said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn100:43.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!"

msgctxt "mn100:43.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
" ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he was righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, just so has Master Gotama made the Teaching clear "
"in many ways."

msgctxt "mn100:43.4"
msgid "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn100:43.5"
msgid ""
"Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn100:43.6"
msgid "Saṅgāravasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "mn100:43.7"
msgid "Brāhmaṇavaggo niṭṭhito pañcamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:43.8"
msgid "Brahmāyu selassalāyano,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn100:43.9"
msgid "ghoṭamukho ca brāhmaṇo;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn100:43.10"
msgid "Caṅkī esu dhanañjāni,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn100:43.11"
msgid "vāseṭṭho subhagāravoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "mn100:43.12"
msgid "Vaggo gahapati bhikkhu,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn100:43.13"
msgid "paribbājakanāmako;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn100:43.14"
msgid "Rājavaggo brāhmaṇoti,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn100:43.15"
msgid "pañca majjhimaāgame."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "mn100:43.16"
msgid "Majjhimapaṇṇāsakaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr ""
